name: Favourite Shoes Gocco Print
description:
A two-colour Gocco print called Favourite Shoes. The day is always that little bit brighter when you're wearing your favourite shoes, isn't it? This is an original, hand-pulled print from a limited edition of 250 that is signed and numbered. I originally made this piece for a Gocco exhibition and printed a small edition in burgundy and light green. I liked it so much, I decided to make a second edition in one of my favourite colour combinations - red and pale blue (I love red shoes!). It's printed on an absolutely beautiful 230 gsm recycled, acid-free card stock which is a lovely eggshell colour with little blue & red flecks - it really does resemble a speckled egg. The print could easily be matted for an 8x10 inch frame or larger, or trimmed down to fit a 5x7 inch frame. Print Gocco is a small-format Japanese screen-printing system that creates unique effects different to conventional screen-printing; kind of a cross between a screen and relief print, with beautiful textures and variations. Details: Sheet size 5.85x8.25 inch (A5 148.5x210 mm) Print area 4.2x5.8 inch (106x147 mm) approx. Edition size: 250 Signed and numbered on the front Please note: due to the fact that they are hand-printed, there may be some minor variations between prints. Each print is packaged with foam-core backing in a clear resealable cello sleeve. Take a look at other products in this range. All designs are unique, original and exclusive to Magic Jelly, and handmade in South Australia.

name: White Swan Ring
description:
An oval adjustable ring from the blue and white series called The Woodlanders, featuring a white swan swimming beneath the willows, set within glassy, jewellery grade resin. This jewellery range is an expression of my passion for paper and ink. I love the way the resin magnifies the paper textures and printed images, transforming them into shining little gems preserved within the resin's glassy depths. With a background in digital art and printmaking, I'm focused on the quality of my printed artwork, and choose beautiful fine art papers to suit the style and printing process of each piece. For this ring I have chosen a lightly textured 100% cotton rag fine art paper that delivers rich colour and fine, crisp detail. Details: Resin-filled oval cabochon 1.2x0.9 inch (30x24 mm) Platinum-plated adjustable ring Gift box 1.7x1.4x1.7 inch (43x36x43 mm) Please note: this is a hand-crafted item so there may be slight variations between the pictured ring and the one you purchase. Part of the nature of hand-poured resin is that it may sometimes contain small bubbles, but this will not detract from the appearance and quality of the finished piece. Visit the Shop Info page for instructions on how to care for your resin jewellery purchase. Take a look at other products in this range. All designs are unique, original and exclusive to Magic Jelly, and handcrafted in South Australia.

name: Magic Circles No. 1 Bracelet
description:
Inspired by the Magic Circles collage series, a wearable version, celebrating vintage ephemera. This handcrafted silver-plated bracelet features twelve images, set within glassy, jewellery grade resin.. Glass flower and leaf charms add that final sparkly flourish. This is a one of a kind piece - the images are original vintage ephemera, not digital reproductions. The paper I've sourced to make this bracelet includes a snippet of wallpaper, cigar labels, a page from an old book, comic strip, map, playing card, invoice, and a matchbox and product label. This jewellery range is an expression of my passion for paper and ink. I love the way the resin magnifies the paper textures and printed images, transforming them into shining little gems preserved within the resin's glassy depths.
